Court of Appeal President Daniel Musinga. [File, Standard]  A seven-member Court of Appeal bench will, by end of Friday, August 20, deliver its ruling on the BBI appeal.  The judges are each reading their verdicts independently.  The seven judges are: Daniel Musinga, Fatuma Sichale, Gatembu Kairu, Hannah Okwengu, Roselyn Nambuye, Patrick Kiage and Francis Tuiyott. Help us serve you better by completing our quick survey. As of 1:40pm, three judges (Francis Tuiyott, Fatuma Sichale and Gatembu Kairu) had read out their verdicts.  BBI verdict: Differences in IEBC quorum arise  Constitutional changes in Kenya since independence  Live Blog: The BBI judgement  BBI judgement: Terms you need to know  The bench proceeded on a one-hour break, and are rescheduled to return at 2:40pm, when the remaining four judges will read out their judgements.  So far, Justices Sichale, Tuiyott and Kairu made the following decisions:  FATUMA SICHALE  FRANCIS TUIYOTT  GATEMBU KAIRU   BBI Case set to go to Court of Appeal with spotlight on the Judicial bench  What does the court's verdict on BBI portend for the three top leaders, Uhuru, Ruto and Raila?  BBI ruling elicits mixed reactions; DP Ruto allies welcome court verdict By Betty Njeru | 55 minutes ago By The Standard | 4 hours ago By Amos Kareithi | 5 hours ago By Willis Oketch | 6 hours ago